===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|onomatopoeia}} The sound made by an object hitting a [[liquid]].
#: ''I heard a '''splash''' when the rock landed in the pond.''
# A small amount of liquid.
#* {{quote-web|en|passage=Add the tomato purée and cook for a further 4-5 minutes. Add a '''splash''' of whisky to the pan, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan with a wooden spoon to deglaze.|url=https://archive.is/20130707023416/www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/grilledfilletofhalib_92475|title=recipe, Grilled fillet of halibut and langoustine tails with smoked haddock risotto and shellfish froth|author=Chris Morrison}}
#: ''I felt a '''splash''' of rain, so I put up my hood.''
#: ''I felt a '''splash''' of water on my leg as the car drove into the nearby puddle.''
# A small amount (of color).
#: ''The painter put a '''splash''' of blue on the wall to make it more colorful''
# A mark or stain made from a small amount of liquid.
#: ''There was a visible '''splash''' on his pants after he went to the bathroom.''
# An [[impact]] or [[impression]].
#: ''The new movie made quite a '''splash''' upon its release.''
# {{lb|en|computing|informal}} A [[splash screen]].
#* '''2008''', Ron Carswell, Heidi Webb, ''Guide to Microsoft Virtual PC 2007 and Virtual Server 2005''
#*: When the '''splash''' appears with Please wait, wait for Windows to start configuration.
# {{lb|en|wrestling}} A [[body press]]; a move where the wrestler jumps forward from a raised platform such as the top [[turnbuckle]], landing [[stomach]] first across an opponent lying on the ground below.
# {{lb|en|dated}} A [[cosmetic]] [[powder]] to [[whiten]] the [[complexion]].
# {{lb|en|journalism}} A large, [[prominent]] [[headline]] or [[article]].
#* '''2006''', Bob Franklin, ''Local Journalism and Local Media: Making the Local News''
#*: So for a local newspaper, a '''splash''' on a fatal crash is just the first of a series of reports.
#* '''2019''', Victoria Hoffarth, ''When Turtles Come Home'' (page 69)
#*: After the brouhaha and the newspaper headline '''splashes''', each of these contentious items would simply die its own quiet death to be replaced by a newer scandal: {{...}}
# {{lb|en|MLE|slang}} A [[bleeding]] caused by a [[knife]] [[wound]].
#* {{quote-song|en|lyricist=Td of TPL|title=Stop Check|url=https://genius.com/Tpl-stop-check-lyrics|date=2020-07-02|note=1:52–1:56|passage=Jojo caught up and gave him a '''splash'''<br/>Slap that wap, get rid of them plats}}
# {{lb|en|MLE|slang}} A [[knife]].
#: {{syn|en|splasher|[[jooka]] ~ [[jooker]]|nank|shank|bassy|rambo|pokey|chete|ying}}
#* {{quote-song|en|author=#CO CMoney|title=Don’t Ask|date=13-08-2021|note=2:51–2:53|passage=You grip your '''splash''' for fashion—me and you, we ain’t got the same intentions.}}

