===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To hit or [[agitate]] liquid so that part of it separates from the principal liquid mass.
#: {{ux|en|sit and '''splash''' in the bathtub}}
#* '''1990''' October 28, [[w:Paul Simon|Paul Simon]], “She Moves On”, ''[[w:The Rhythm of the Saints|The Rhythm of the Saints]]'', Warner Bros.
#*: I know the reason I feel so blessed / My heart still '''splashes''' inside my chest
# To disperse a fluid suddenly; to [[splatter]].
#: {{ux|en|water '''splashed''' everywhere}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To hit or expel liquid at.
#: {{ux|en|The children were '''splashing''' each other playfully in the sea.}}
#: {{ux|en|When she comes in the door, '''splash''' her with perfume.}}
# To create an impact or [[impression]]; to print, post or [[publicize]] [[prominent]]ly.
#: {{ux|en|The headline was '''splashed''' across newspapers everywhere.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[spend]] (money).
#: {{ux|en|After pay day I can afford to '''splash''' some cash and buy myself a motorbike.}}
# {{lb|en|figurative}} {{rfdef|en}}
#*{{quote-web|en|date=July 6 2021|work=BBC Sport|author={{w|Phil McNulty}}|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/57743513|title=Italy beat Spain on penalties: 'Pure theatre as Italy present formidable obstacle in final'|passage=This was pure theatre, with a 60,000 crowd at Wembley adding colour to the fight to face either England or Denmark in Sunday's final, the stadium '''splashed''' with the red of Spain at one end and the victorious blue of Italy at the other as crowds flocked back in ever bigger numbers after pandemic restrictions were lifted.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|nautical}} To [[launch]] a ship.
#* '''1999''' David M. Kennedy, ''"Victory at Sea"'', ''Atlantic Monthly'', March 1999:
#*: In the two years following Midway, Japanese shipyards managed to '''splash''' only six additional fleet carriers. The United States in the same period added seventeen, along with ten medium carriers and eighty-six escort carriers.
# {{lb|en|military|slang}} To [[shoot down]] (an [[aircraft]]) over [[water]].
#: {{ux|en|The cruiser's AA gun crews managed to '''splash''' all of the three kamikazes headed towards the ship.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|MLE}} To [[stab]] (a person), causing them to [[bleed]].
#* {{quote-song|en|date=18-10-2017|lyricist=Knockoutned|artist=#Moscow17 Ruth x Knockoutned|title=Panic|passage=Grab him, dont panic, rambo under my jacket<br/>Nap him, '''splash''' him, then I'm petrol bath my jacket}}

